Module com.example.schedulejawn
Package controller

Class MainController

java.lang.Object
controller.MainController
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.fxml.Initializable
public class MainController extends Object implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
The class handles user interaction in main.fxml. User gains access to the customer and appointment tables. User can add, edit, and delete customer and appointment. User can access the reports requested - appointments per contact, appointments per type and appointments per month. Total customers per country was the third report choice. Home is currently a work in progress.

    • initialize

      public void initialize(URL url, ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
      Method initializes the main controller. Lambda #1: The lambda here is used to format the zonedatetime of localdatetime. Customer, appointment, contact, report tables are set in this method. Home is selected as the start of the main screen.
      Specified by:
      initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
      Parameters:
      url -
      resourceBundle -

    • mainToggleButton

      public void mainToggleButton(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      Method handles what is available to the user based on the selection of customer, appointment or report. Selecting customer will show only customer stuff. Selecting appointment will show only appointment stuff. Selecting report will show only report stuff. Lambda #2: The lambda expressions are declared outside the method due to being used in another method. The lambda expressions are created to hide components on the main.fxml based on the toggle button chosen. It has helped reduced the repetitiveness that existed prior to using lambda expressions.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - one of the toggle buttons is selected

    • reportToggleAction

      public void reportToggleAction(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      Method handles what the user will see based on the selection made in the report. Productivity toggle button shows the type, month and country table reports. Contact toggle button shows the contact table where user can select the contact from a combobox to see the appts for the selected contact.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - a toggle button is selected

    • clickedAdd

      public void clickedAdd(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      Method handles which add screen pops up based on the selected toggle button. Customer button selected leads to the add customer fxml. Appt button selected leads to the add appt fxml.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - add button clicked
      Throws:
      IOException

    • clickedEdit

      public void clickedEdit(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      Method handles which edit screen is shown based on the selected toggle button - customer or appt. Customer button selected leads to editCustomer fxml. Appt button selected leads to editAppt fxml.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - edit button clicked
      Throws:
      IOException

    • clickedDelete

      public void clickedDelete(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws SQLException
      Method deletes customer or appt based on the selected toggle button. Customer is checked for any existing appts before delete. If customer has appt, error will inform user of deleting appt before customer deletion. Appt deletion is proceeded with a refresh of the view all, view month and view week data.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - delete button clicked
      Throws:
      SQLException

    • apptDifferViewsRadioButtons

      public void apptDifferViewsRadioButtons(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      Method handles what is being presented in the appointment table based on the radiobutton chosen. View all radio button shows all appts. View week radio button shows appts for that week. View month radio button shows appts for that month.

    • selectedContactForContactReportTable

      public void selectedContactForContactReportTable(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      Method sets the table with appointments per the selected contact.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - selected contact from the contact combobox
